{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban house viewings if the tenant does not approve during the pandemic",
        "additional_details": "I am currently renting a house, the landlord has put it up for sale with me still as a tenant. In my lease it states I must let people in to view the property at the landlords request.  They are demanding I allow people in often with there parents and the estate agent all at the same time.",
        "background": "Currently if it is in a lease that a tenant has to allow a landlord entry to a property for viewings if they put the property on the market for sale, the tenant must grant access letting in estate agents, and prospective purchasers.  It isn't right during lockdowns!",
